author: NEW YORK DAILY NEWS
title: Celebrity makeup artist found dead in L.A. home: report
text:
byjakebailey via Instagram Makeup artist Jake Bailey, whose talent was trusted by singers Katy Perry and Selena Gomez, pictured, was found dead in his Los Angeles home on Friday. byjakebailey via Instagram The 37-year-old is seen applying Katy Perry's makeup. byjakebailey via Instagram Jake Bailey, whose talent was trusted by singers Katy Perry and Selena Gomez, was found dead in his Los Angeles home on Friday. Previous Next Enlarge A beloved makeup artist to the stars was reportedly found dead in his Los Angeles home from a suspected suicide.
Jake Bailey, whose talent was trusted by the likes of Katy Perry, Selena Gomez, Mariah Carey, and Emmy Rossum, is believed to have died from carbon monoxide poisoning, TMZ reported.
The 37-year-old was found dead by his assistant Friday morning. The tragic discovery came just hours after he apparently posted an Instagram photo of himself smiling.
Matt Jones/ Cosmopolitan Bailey applied Perry's makeup for her July 2014 Cosmopolitan cover as well as for her Super Bowl halftime performance.
Some of Bailey's cosmetic masterpieces includes Perry's shimmering green and rainbow Cosmopolitan cover and her makeup during her Super Bowl XLIX halftime performance.
Among those immediately expressing their heartbreak over his loss was actress Emmy Rossum.
"I am gutted to hear of my friend Jake's passing. I saw him on Sunday, we flew together on a plane. He made me laugh as always," she tweeted.
"I will miss his sense of humor, talent and kindness. If there are angels in heaven, they just got a little prettier... because Jake is up there painting their faces... putting lashes on them..."
